# EV Engine Rules

## compute_ev() — always pass `stat=`

Every call to `compute_ev()` must include `stat=<stat_key>` so temperature-scaling calibration is applied. Missing `stat=` silently skips calibration.

## Distribution modes

- Poisson: `stl`, `blk`, `fg3m`, `tov`
- Normal CDF: `pts`, `reb`, `ast`, `pra`
- Reference mode bypasses distribution

## Stat priority

`pts > reb > ast > pra > tov >> stl > fg3m > blk`

## Book priority

`BetMGM > DraftKings > FanDuel` — all `--books` flags and line selection follow this order.

## BETTING_POLICY gate

- Stat whitelist: `{pts, reb, ast, pra}`
- Blocked confidence bins: `{4, 5}` (40-60%)
- `min_edge_threshold`: 0.05 (no-vig edge)
- `blk` and `fg3m`: structural Poisson bias — do not act on >60% model confidence until recalibrated

## Edge verdicts

| Edge | Verdict |
|------|---------|
| < 0 | Negative EV |
| < 0.05 | Thin Edge |
| 0.05 - 0.08 | Good Value |
| >= 0.08 | Strong Value |

## CLV rule

High-quality bet requires `clvLine > 0` AND `clvOddsPct > 0`. Positive model EV alone is not sufficient.
